                </fr:date>
                <fr:addr>forest://forester/jms-011T</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/jms-011T.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Forester 5.0 [TBA] › simplifications to the source language › removing transclusion overrides"><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/OYOT.xml" title="Forester 5.0 [TBA] › simplifications to the source language" addr="forest://forester/OYOT" type="local"><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/jms-011P.xml" title="Forester 5.0 [TBA]" addr="forest://forester/jms-011P" type="local">Forester 5.0 [TBA]</fr:link> › simplifications to the source language</fr:link> › removing transclusion overrides</fr:title>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>In prior versions of Forester, it was possible to override the title and the taxon of a transcluded tree using the fluid bindings <html:code><![CDATA[\transclude/title]]></html:code> and <html:code><![CDATA[\transclude/taxon]]></html:code> respectively. This feature is no longer supported in <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/jms-011P.xml" title="Forester 5.0 [TBA]" addr="forest://forester/jms-011P" type="local">Forester 5.0 [TBA]</fr:link>, and existing users are encouraged to purge their use of it prior to upgrading to <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/jms-011P.xml" title="Forester 5.0 [TBA]" addr="forest://forester/jms-011P" type="local">Forester 5.0 [TBA]</fr:link>.</html:p>
                <html:p>In short, supporting this feature was greatly complicating the planned transition to a genuine hypermedia format; it could also be argued that it might have led to scenarios where an original author’s intentions are violated at the transclusion site.</html:p>
                <html:p>Please note that transclusion options, such as <html:code><![CDATA[\transclude/expanded]]></html:code>, etc., are still supported.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
