      <fr:mainmatter>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="forest://forester/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
              <fr:month>10</fr:month>
              <fr:day>20</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:addr>forest://forester/jms-0126</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/jms-0126.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Forester 5.0 [TBA] › tl;dr: migration guide"><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/jms-011P.xml" title="Forester 5.0 [TBA]" addr="forest://forester/jms-011P" type="local">Forester 5.0 [TBA]</fr:link> › tl;dr: migration guide</fr:title>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>To migrate your forest to <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/jms-011P.xml" title="Forester 5.0 [TBA]" addr="forest://forester/jms-011P" type="local">Forester 5.0 [TBA]</fr:link>, do the following:</html:p>
            <html:ol><html:li>Add a <html:code>host = "myforestname"</html:code> line to your <html:code>forest.toml</html:code> (see <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/jms-011Q.xml" title="Forester 5.0 [TBA] › a URL scheme for tree addresses" addr="forest://forester/jms-011Q" type="local">§ <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://forester/jms-011Q" /></fr:link>). Most users of Forester will use their own name as the host of their main forest, e.g. <html:code>host = "jonmsterling"</html:code>.</html:li>
  <html:li>Remove all usage of <html:code><![CDATA[\transclude/title]]></html:code> and <html:code><![CDATA[\transclude/taxon]]></html:code> (see <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/jms-011T.xml" title="Forester 5.0 [TBA] › simplifications to the source language › removing transclusion overrides" addr="forest://forester/jms-011T" type="local">§ <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://forester/jms-011T" /></fr:link>).</html:li>
  <html:li>Move all <html:code><![CDATA[\import]]></html:code> declarations to the top-level of any <html:code>.tree</html:code> files, as these can no longer occur in subtrees (see <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/OYOU.xml" title="Forester 5.0 [TBA] › simplifications to the source language › removal of imports within subtrees" addr="forest://forester/OYOU" type="local">§ <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://forester/OYOU" /></fr:link>).</html:li>
  <html:li>In your <html:code>forest.toml</html:code> file, change the <html:code>root = "xxx-NNNN"</html:code> line to <html:code>home = "xxx-NNNN"</html:code>, where <html:code>xxx-NNNN</html:code> is the name of the tree that you wish to be routed to <html:code>index.xml</html:code> (see <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/jms-0125.xml" title="Forester 5.0 [TBA] › renamed root to home" addr="forest://forester/jms-0125" type="local">§ <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://forester/jms-0125" /></fr:link>).</html:li>
  <html:li>Any <html:code><![CDATA[\author]]></html:code> or <html:code><![CDATA[\contributor]]></html:code> attributions must take a tree address as their argument; when you wish to attribute a resource to a person who is not represented by a tree, you can use <html:code><![CDATA[\author/literal{Somebody’s Name}]]></html:code> or <html:code><![CDATA[\contributor/literal{Somebody’s Name}]]></html:code> (see <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/jms-012N.xml" title="Forester 5.0 [TBA] › Changes to attribution links" addr="forest://forester/jms-012N" type="local">§ <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://forester/jms-012N" /></fr:link>).</html:li>
  <html:li>Take into account the renaming of several built-in relations (see <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/jms-013C.xml" title="Forester 5.0 [TBA] › new datalog-based query engine › renamed built-in relations" addr="forest://forester/jms-013C" type="local">§ <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://forester/jms-013C" /></fr:link>).</html:li>
  <html:li>Begin rewriting any queries to use the new datalog engine (see <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/jms-013A.xml" title="Forester 5.0 [TBA] › new datalog-based query engine" addr="forest://forester/jms-013A" type="local">§ <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://forester/jms-013A" /></fr:link>), as the legacy query engine will be removed in a subsequent release.</html:li>
  <html:li>Begin dialing back your use of custom XML stylesheets (see <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/jms-0127.xml" title="Forester 5.0 [TBA] › the future of Forester’s XML format" addr="forest://forester/jms-0127" type="local">§ <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://forester/jms-0127" /></fr:link>). It is possible that support for customisation at this level will be removed in a future release; if you have innovative customisations that are very important for your use of Forester, consider discussing them on the <fr:link href="mailto:~jonsterling/forester-discuss@lists.sr.ht" type="external">mailing list</fr:link> so that maintainers can better understand the problems you are solving.</html:li></html:ol>
          </fr:mainmatter>
